results.summary: Technical Assistance to operationalise the Capacity Building & Engagement Window of the “Enhancing Accountability” programme
results.content: Technical Assistance to operationalise the Capacity Building & Engagement Window of the “Enhancing Accountability” programme

description: The EUD to South Africa requires technical assistance (TA) to set up, manage and implement the “Enhancing Accountability” programme’s Capacity Building & Engagement Window.The Capacity Building & Engagement Window will provide resources, support and opportunities for state and NSA to enhance participation, accountability and non-discrimination and transparency in the public and private sphere in South Africa. The Window will make resources available for: (1) Exchange of Experiences; (2) Mobilisation of Experts; (3) Research and studies; (4) Training and capacity building including short term exchanges; (5) Conferences, seminars, workshops, etc. The Window will also provide a platform for knowledge sharing, peer evaluation, thematic dialogues, sector coordination and dialogue in a sustainable way.  The TA will operationalise the Window, communication, visibility and outreach activities, monitoring and evaluation, and will take guidance from the EU Delegation and the Advisory Committee.
title: Technical Assistance to operationalise the Capacity Building & Engagement Window of the “Enhancing Accountability” programme

results.content: Nation Branding Strategy Development and Implementation (Rwanda)

description: The objective of this contract is to improve Rwanda's competitiveness, and attract further interest to its products and services on the global scene. The Nation Branding Strategy will communicate Rwanda’s economic development milestones achieved over the last two decades with a focus on various sectors of the country’s economy. It will also showcase the strategic investment opportunities in various growth sectors such as sustainable tourism and conservation, agro-processing, Information and Communications Technology (ICT), infrastructure, and export promotion among others. results.summary: Supporting the impact assessment on the effects of mid- and long-term IMO climate measures on the Pacific Island countries, and advancing effective partnerships in IMO climate change related meetings
results.content: Supporting the impact assessment on the effects of mid- and long-term IMO climate measures on the Pacific Island countries, and advancing effective partnerships in IMO climate change related meetings

description: This action aims to support ambitious climate action in IMO by strengthening the Pacific Island States (PIS) in the organisation and their effective co-operation with the EU. The objective is to enable PIS to prepare for and participate in IMO, so they can actively support an ambitious revision of the IMO GHG strategy and contribute to the assessment of mid- and long-term IMO climate measures. For this, the project will fund a study to identify and analyse data on PIS which will be used to assess the impacts of future measures. A shortage of data from the region complicates the assessment of the effects of the measures, which the study will remedy. Secondly, this project will organise regional workshops and high-level meetings to facilitate shared EU-Pacific position in the negotiations on IMO, and provide technical assistance for PIS. The meetings will take place in 2023 and 2024. The action supports existing and successful EU-Pacific co-operation.
title: Supporting the impact assessment on the effects of mid- and long-term IMO climate measures on the Pacific Island countries, and advancing effective partnerships in IMO climate change related meetings

results.summary: Enhancement of the operation of hydropower plant of Litani River Authority (LRA), Machgara,West Bekaa, Lebanon
results.content: Enhancement of the operation of hydropower plant of Litani River Authority (LRA), Machgara,West Bekaa, Lebanon

description: The Abdel Al Hydropower Plant feeds the overall EDL grid in power and has a substation providing power to 93 villages in Bekaa and South Lebanon.The Abdel Al Hydropower Plant (MARKABI HPP) is the first hydropower plant on Litani River located in West Bekaa near the village of Machgara. Since 1962, its installed capacity is 2x18 MW and it is the master of the cascade of hydroelectric power Plants formed by the following power stations: MARKABI (2x18MW), AWALI (3x36 MW) and JOUN (2x24 MW). The Electric Protection System (EPS) is an essential component of the plant equipment. It consists of a series of electrical relays that protect the grid from electric shortcuts and damage. By time, the EPS is consumed and needs to be replaced to protect the plant from damage
title: Enhancement of the operation of hydropower plant of Litani River Authority (LRA), Machgara,West Bekaa, Lebanon

results.summary: Establishment of Law Enforcement Record Management System
results.content: Establishment of Law Enforcement Record Management System

description: Establishment of an IT Tool: Law Enforcement Record Management System (LERMS) at the Law Enforcement Agencies (LEAs) of the Republic of North Macedonia that will ensure record management and tracking of records of law enforcement operations and investigations in suppressing organized crime, corruption, terrorism and other types of crime; providing analytical functionalities for generating structured data and supplementing the data exchange by different LEA with reliable data. The contractor will: i) conduct a Gap Analysis  and assessment of the current institutional setup and IT infrastructure used by LEAs for record management of criminal cases, ii) develop a software solution –LERMS– and establish its full functionality  at the Beneficiary Institutions, preparing procedures for maintenance of the system and all technical documentation and providing trainings, and iii) prepare the  legal framework for functioning and usage of the system by the LEAs.
title: Establishment of Law Enforcement Record Management System

results.summary: Türkiye’s Net Zero Emission Target: Road Map for Transport
results.content: Türkiye’s Net Zero Emission Target: Road Map for Transport

description: The purpose of the contract is to develop the national roadmap for transport sector including Strategy, Action Plan and Pathways for net zero emissions target with concrete policies, solutions/actions, defined indicators and milestone. The contract will also include development of a Green Project Pipeline (GPP) and related financing framework. The contract shall be based on; but not necessarily be limited to:1. Roadmap for transport sector including Strategy, Action Plan and Pathways;2. Capacity development for implementation of Roadmap;3. Publicity and visibility;4. Green Project Pipeline (GPP) including priority and secondary projects/actions proposals and their financing framework.
title: Türkiye’s Net Zero Emission Target: Road Map for Transport

results.summary: Support and Assistance to Strengthen the Capabilities of the Belarusian Nuclear Regulatory Authority (BY3.01/20A)
results.content: Support and Assistance to Strengthen the Capabilities of the Belarusian Nuclear Regulatory Authority (BY3.01/20A)

description: The scope of the contract includes the provision of services in order to support the Belarusian regulatory authority to improve its capabilities and capacities in the following areas:1) Licensing of safety enhancement measures introduced at Belarusian Nuclear Power Plant (BelNPP) as the results of the EU stress-tests;2) Oversight and regulatory control of radiation and nuclear safety at BelNPP in its early phase of operation;3) Oversight and regulatory control of emergency preparedness and response (EP&R) at BelNPP;4) Assessing operational experience accumulated at the BelNPP;5) Enhancing regulatory technical capabilities in reviewing deterministic and probabilistic safety analyses, as well as performing its own independent assessments;6) Development of legislative provisions for regulating the operation of nuclear installations.
title: Support and Assistance to Strengthen the Capabilities of the Belarusian Nuclear Regulatory Authority (BY3.01/20A)
